   36: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
   37: %% Initializations
   38: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
   39: 
   40: %-define(dont_rm_test_dirs, true).
   41: 
   42: -ifndef(dont_rm_test_dirs).
   43: 
   44: init_per_suite(Config) ->
   45:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   46:     ok = erl_tar:extract("xmlts20130923.tar.gz", [compressed]),
   47:     Dirs = ["ibm","japanese","oasis","sun","xmltest"],
   48:     [file:rename("xmlconf/" ++ Dir, Dir) || Dir <- Dirs],
   49:     [ok = erl_tar:extract(Dir ++ ".tgz", [compressed]) || Dir <- Dirs],
   50:     ok = change_mode(Dirs),
   51:     [{timetrap,{seconds, 1}}|Config].
   52: 
   53: end_per_suite(Config) ->
   54:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   55:     ok=rm_files(["ibm","japanese","oasis","sun","xmltest"]),
   56:     Config.
   57: 
   58: -else.
   59: 
   60: init_per_suite(Config) ->
   61:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   62:     [{timetrap,{seconds, 1}}|Config].
   63: 
   64: end_per_suite(Config) ->
   65:     Config.
   66: 
   67: -endif.
   68: 
   69: %% initialization before each testcase
   70: init_per_testcase(_TestCase,Config) ->
   71:     io:format("Config:\n~p\n",[Config]),
   72:     {ok, _} = file:read_file_info(filename:join([privdir(Config)])),
   73:     code:add_patha(privdir(Config)),
   74:     Config.
   75:  
   76: %% clean up after each testcase
   77: end_per_testcase(_Func,_Config) ->
   78:     ok.
   79:

   89: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
   90: %% Test Case 
   91: %% Uri: not-wf/sa/001.xml
   92: %% ID: not-wf-sa-001
   93: %% Type: not-wf
   94: %% Sections: 3.1 [41]
   95: %% Description:
   96: %%   Attribute values must start with attribute names, not "?".
   97: 'not-wf-sa-001'(Config) -> 
   98:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   99:     Path = filename:join([datadir(Config),"xmltest","not-wf/sa/001.xml"]),
  100:     R = xmerl_sax_parser:file(Path, [{external_entities, file}, {event_fun, fun sax_canon/3}]),
  101:     check_result(R, "not-wf").
  102:

29491: init_per_group(_GroupName, Config) ->

29496: 
29497: %%======================================================================
29498: %% Support Functions
29499: %%======================================================================
29500: 
29501: %% Dir is a directory
29502: rm_f_(Dir) ->
29503:     {ok,CWD} = file:get_cwd(),
29504:     {ok,FileList} = file:list_dir(Dir),
29505:     file:set_cwd(filename:join([CWD,Dir])),
29506:     rm_files(FileList),
29507:     file:set_cwd(CWD),
29508:     ? line ok = file:del_dir(Dir).
29509: 
29510: rm_files([])->
29511:     ok;
29512: rm_files([F|Fs]) ->
29513:     case filelib:is_dir(F) of
29514:     true ->
29515:         rm_f_(F);
29516:     _ ->
29517:         ok = file:delete(F)
29518:     end,
29519:     rm_files(Fs).
29520: 
29521: 
29522: change_mode(Files) ->
29523:     change_mode3(Files).
29524: change_mode2(Dir)->
29525:     {ok,CWD} = file:get_cwd(),
29526:     {ok,FileList} = file:list_dir(Dir),
29527:     file:set_cwd(filename:join([CWD,Dir])),
29528:     change_mode3(FileList),
29529:     file:set_cwd(CWD).
29530: change_mode3([]) ->
29531:     ok;
29532: change_mode3([F|Fs]) ->
29533:     case filelib:is_dir(F) of
29534:     true ->
29535:         chmod(F),
29536:         change_mode2(F);
29537:     _ ->
29538:         chmod(F)
29539:     end,
29540:     change_mode3(Fs).
29541:     
29542: chmod(F) ->
29543:     case file:read_file_info(F) of
29544:     {ok,FileInfo} ->
29545:         Mode= FileInfo#file_info.mode,
29546:         file:write_file_info(F,FileInfo#file_info{mode=8#00777 bor Mode});
29547:     _ ->
29548:         ok
29549:     end.
29550: 
29551: privdir(Config) ->
29552:     proplists:get_value(priv_dir, Config).
29553: datadir(Config) ->
29554:     proplists:get_value(data_dir, Config).
29555: 
29556: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
29557: %% check_result 
29558: check_result({fatal_error,_,_,_,_}, "error") -> ok;
29559: check_result({ok, _, _}, "invalid") -> ok;
29560: check_result({fatal_error,_,_,_,_}, "not-wf") -> ok;
29561: check_result({ok, _, _}, "valid") -> ok;
29562: check_result(A, T) -> ct:fail({2, T, A}).
29563: 
29564: check_result({ok, B, _}, "invalid", B) -> ok;
29565: check_result({ok, B, _}, "valid", B) -> ok;
29566: check_result({ok, B, _}, "error", B) -> ok;
29567: check_result(A, T, B) -> ct:fail({3, T, A, B}).
29568: 
29569: sax_canon({startElement, _, _, {Prefix, LocalName}, Attributes},_,{S, Es}) ->
29570:        LName = unicode:characters_to_binary(LocalName),
29571:        Name = case Prefix of
29572:              [] ->
29573:                 LName;
29574:              _ ->
29575:                 Px = unicode:characters_to_binary(Prefix),
29576:                 <<Px/binary, $:, LName/binary>>
29577:           end,
29578:        Atts = <<
29579:             begin
29580:                 AName = 
29581:                     case APrefix of
29582:                         [] -> 
29583:                             unicode:characters_to_binary(AttributeName);
29584:                         _ ->
29585:                             P = unicode:characters_to_binary(APrefix),
29586:                             L = unicode:characters_to_binary(AttributeName),
29587:                             <<P/binary, $:, L/binary>>
29588:                     end,
29589:                 Val = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Value)),
29590:                 <<" ", AName/binary, "=\"", Val/binary, "\"">>
29591:             end
29592:             ||
29593:             {_, APrefix, AttributeName, Value} <- lists:sort(Attributes)
29594:             >>,
29595:        {<<S/binary, $<, Name/binary, Atts/binary, $>>>, [element|Es]};
29596: sax_canon({endElement, _, _, {Prefix, LocalName}},_, {S, [_|Es]}) ->
29597:        LName = unicode:characters_to_binary(LocalName),
29598:        Name = case Prefix of
29599:              [] ->
29600:                 LName;
29601:              _ ->
29602:                 Px = unicode:characters_to_binary(Prefix),
29603:                 <<Px/binary, $:, LName/binary>>
29604:           end,
29605:        {<<S/binary, "</" , Name/binary, ">">>, Es};
29606: sax_canon({characters, Str},_,{S, Es}) -> 
29607:     Bin = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Str)),
29608:     {<<S/binary, Bin/binary>>, Es};
29609: sax_canon({ignorableWhitespace, Str},_,{S, [element|_] = Es}) -> 
29610:     Bin = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Str)),
29611:     {<<S/binary, Bin/binary>>, Es};
29612: sax_canon({processingInstruction, Target, Data},_,{S, Es}) -> 
29613:     T = unicode:characters_to_binary(Target),
29614:     case Data of
29615:            [] ->
29616:               {<<S/binary, "<?", T/binary, " ?>">>, Es};
29617:            _ ->
29618:               D = unicode:characters_to_binary(Data),
29619:               {<<S/binary, "<?", T/binary, " ", D/binary, "?>">>, Es}
29620:     end;
29621: sax_canon(startDocument,_,_) -> {<<>>, []};
29622: sax_canon(endDocument,_,{S, _}) -> S;
29623: sax_canon({startDTD, _, _, _} = E,_,{S, []}) -> {S, [E]};
29624: sax_canon(endDTD,_,{S, Es}) -> 
29625:     % report any notations
29626:     case Es of
29627:         [_] ->
29628:             {S, []};
29629:         _ ->
29630:            [{startDTD, Name, _PublicId, _SystemId}|Ns] = lists:reverse(Es),
29631:            F = fun({notationDecl, NName, PublicId, []}) ->
29632:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29633:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(PublicId),
29634:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " PUBLIC '", BId/binary, "'>">>;
29635:                   ({notationDecl, NName, [], SystemId}) ->
29636:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29637:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(SystemId),
29638:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " SYSTEM '", BId/binary, "'>">>;
29639:                   ({notationDecl, NName, PublicId, SystemId}) ->
29640:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29641:                      PId = unicode:characters_to_binary(PublicId),
29642:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(SystemId),
29643:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " PUBLIC '", PId/binary, "' '", BId/binary, "'>">>
29644:                end,
29645:            Sort = fun({_,A,_,_},{_,B,_,_}) -> A =< B end,
29646:            Nots = iolist_to_binary(lists:map(F, lists:sort(Sort, Ns))),
29647:            DName = unicode:characters_to_binary(Name),
29648:            Db = <<S/binary, "<!DOCTYPE ", DName/binary, " [",
29649:                   Nots/binary,
29650:                   "\n]>\n">>,
29651:            {Db, []}
29652:     end;
29653: sax_canon({notationDecl, _, _, _} = E,_,{S, Es}) -> 
29654:    {S, [E|Es]};
29655: sax_canon(_,_,S) -> S.
29656: 
29657: norm_chars(Bin) ->
29658:     <<
29659:     case C of
29660:         9 -> <<"&#9;">>;
29661:         10 -> <<"&#10;">>;
29662:         13 -> <<"&#13;">>;
29663:         $< -> <<"&lt;">>;
29664:         $> -> <<"&gt;">>;
29665:         38 -> <<"&amp;">>;
29666:         $" -> <<"&quot;">>;
29667:         _ ->
29668:            <<C/utf8>>
29669:     end || <<C/utf8>> <= Bin >>.
